The paper proposes a method for image super-resolution, which is a common problem in computer vision and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The method uses sparse signal representation, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT). The method also involves block matching, which is a technique used in image processing and computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves selecting informative low-resolution images, which can be seen as a form of feature selection, a common problem in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
